  "notes": [
    "This case report describes an unusual presentation of ACTH-dependent Cushing syndrome with discordant peripheral and central responses to desmopressin stimulation.",
    "The patient developed acute adrenal insufficiency following cabergoline treatment, which resolved upon discontinuation of the drug.",
    "Bilateral adrenalectomy was ultimately required for definitive treatment of persistent hypercortisolism."
  ]
